#: ../../user/introduction.rst:3
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "簡介"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:5
msgid "Table of Contents"
msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:8
msgid "What This Is"
msgstr "這是什麼"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:10
msgid ""
"Welcome to Spinning Up in Deep RL! This is an educational resource "
"produced by OpenAI that makes it easier to learn about deep reinforcement"
" learning (deep RL)."
msgstr ""
"歡迎來到 Spinning Up in Deep RL！這是一份由 OpenAI 製作的教育資源，"
"旨在幫助你更輕鬆地學習深度強化學習 (Deep Reinforcement Learning, deep RL)。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:12
msgid ""
"For the unfamiliar: `reinforcement learning`_ (RL) is a machine learning "
"approach for teaching agents how to solve tasks by trial and error. Deep "
"RL refers to the combination of RL with `deep learning`_."
msgstr ""
"如果你還不熟悉：`reinforcement learning`_（強化學習，Reinforcement Learning，RL）"
"是一種機器學習 (Machine Learning) 方法，透過試誤法 (Trial and Error) 來教導"
"代理人 (Agent) 如何解決任務。Deep RL 指的是將 RL 與\\ `deep learning`_"
"（深度學習，Deep Learning）相結合。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:14
msgid "This module contains a variety of helpful resources, including:"
msgstr "本模組包含多種實用資源，包括："

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:16
msgid ""
"a short `introduction`_ to RL terminology, kinds of algorithms, and basic"
" theory,"
msgstr ""
"一份簡短的 RL 術語、演算法 (Algorithm) 類型與基礎理論的\\ `introduction`_\\ ，"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:17
msgid "an `essay`_ about how to grow into an RL research role,"
msgstr "一篇關於如何成長為 RL 研究者的\\ `essay`_\\ ，"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:18
msgid "a `curated list`_ of important papers organized by topic,"
msgstr "一份按主題整理的重要論文\\ `curated list`_\\ ，"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:19
msgid ""
"a well-documented `code repo`_ of short, standalone implementations of "
"key algorithms,"
msgstr ""
"一個文件齊全的\\ `code repo`_\\ ，包含簡短、獨立的關鍵演算法實作，"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:20
msgid "and a few `exercises`_ to serve as warm-ups."
msgstr "以及一些作為暖身的\\ `exercises`_\\ 。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:27
msgid "Why We Built This"
msgstr "我們為什麼建立這個"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:29
msgid "One of the single most common questions that we hear is"
msgstr "我們最常聽到的問題之一是"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:31
msgid "If I want to contribute to AI safety, how do I get started?"
msgstr "如果我想為 AI 安全做出貢獻，我該如何入門？"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:33
msgid ""
"At OpenAI, we believe that deep learning generally---and deep "
"reinforcement learning specifically---will play central roles in the "
"development of powerful AI technology. To ensure that AI is safe, we have"
" to come up with safety strategies and algorithms that are compatible "
"with this paradigm. As a result, we encourage everyone who asks this "
"question to study these fields."
msgstr ""
"在 OpenAI，我們相信深度學習整體而言——以及深度強化學習具體而言——將在"
"強大 AI 技術的發展中扮演核心角色。為了確保 AI 的安全性，我們必須提出"
"與此範式 (Paradigm) 相容的安全策略 (Policy) 與演算法。因此，我們鼓勵"
"每一位提出這個問題的人去研讀這些領域。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:35
msgid ""
"However, while there are many resources to help people quickly ramp up on"
" deep learning, deep reinforcement learning is more challenging to break "
"into. To begin with, a student of deep RL needs to have some background "
"in math, coding, and regular deep learning. Beyond that, they need both a"
" high-level view of the field---an awareness of what topics are studied "
"in it, why they matter, and what's been done already---and careful "
"instruction on how to connect algorithm theory to algorithm code."
msgstr ""
"然而，儘管有許多資源可以幫助人們快速上手深度學習，深度強化學習卻更難以"
"入門。首先，學習 deep RL 的學生需要具備一些數學、程式設計和一般深度學習"
"的基礎。此外，他們還需要對該領域有全局觀——了解哪些主題正在被研究、"
"為什麼重要、以及已經完成了哪些工作——同時還需要關於如何將演算法理論"
"與演算法程式碼連結起來的詳細指導。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:37
msgid ""
"The high-level view is hard to come by because of how new the field is. "
"There is not yet a standard deep RL textbook, so most of the knowledge is"
" locked up in either papers or lecture series, which can take a long time"
" to parse and digest. And learning to implement deep RL algorithms is "
"typically painful, because either"
msgstr ""
"由於這個領域太新，全局觀很難獲得。目前還沒有標準的 deep RL 教科書，"
"因此大部分知識都封存在論文或系列講座中，需要花很長時間來解讀和消化。"
"而學習實作 deep RL 演算法通常也很痛苦，因為"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:39
msgid ""
"the paper that publishes an algorithm omits or inadvertently obscures key"
" design details,"
msgstr "發表演算法的論文省略或無意中模糊了關鍵的設計細節，"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:40
msgid ""
"or widely-public implementations of an algorithm are hard to read, hiding"
" how the code lines up with the algorithm."
msgstr "或者廣泛公開的演算法實作難以閱讀，隱藏了程式碼與演算法之間的對應關係。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:42
msgid ""
"While fantastic repos like garage_, Baselines_, and rllib_ make it easier"
" for researchers who are already in the field to make progress, they "
"build algorithms into frameworks in ways that involve many non-obvious "
"choices and trade-offs, which makes them hard to learn from. "
"Consequently, the field of deep RL has a pretty high barrier to entry---"
"for new researchers as well as practitioners and hobbyists."
msgstr ""
"雖然像 garage_、Baselines_ 和 rllib_ 這樣優秀的程式庫讓已經在該領域的"
"研究人員更容易取得進展，但它們將演算法構建到框架中的方式涉及許多不明顯"
"的選擇和權衡，這使得它們很難用來學習。因此，deep RL 領域的入門門檻相當"
"高——對於新研究者、實務工作者和業餘愛好者都是如此。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:44
msgid ""
"So our package here is designed to serve as the missing middle step for "
"people who are excited by deep RL, and would like to learn how to use it "
"or make a contribution, but don't have a clear sense of what to study or "
"how to transmute algorithms into code. We've tried to make this as "
"helpful a launching point as possible."
msgstr ""
"因此，我們的這個套件旨在為那些對 deep RL 感到興奮、想要學習如何使用它"
"或做出貢獻、但不清楚該學什麼或如何將演算法轉化為程式碼的人，提供缺失"
"的中間階梯。我們努力使它成為一個盡可能有幫助的起點。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:46
msgid ""
"That said, practitioners aren't the only people who can (or should) "
"benefit from these materials. Solving AI safety will require people with "
"a wide range of expertise and perspectives, and many relevant professions"
" have no connection to engineering or computer science at all. "
"Nonetheless, everyone involved will need to learn enough about the "
"technology to make informed decisions, and several pieces of Spinning Up "
"address that need."
msgstr ""
"話雖如此，實務工作者並不是唯一能夠（或應該）從這些教材中受益的人。"
"解決 AI 安全問題需要具備各種專業知識和觀點的人才，而許多相關職業與工程"
"或電腦科學完全沒有關聯。儘管如此，每個參與者都需要對技術有足夠的了解"
"才能做出明智的決策，而 Spinning Up 的多個部分正是為此需求而設計的。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:51
msgid "How This Serves Our Mission"
msgstr "這如何服務於我們的使命"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:53
msgid ""
"OpenAI's mission_ is to ensure the safe development of AGI and the broad "
"distribution of benefits from AI more generally. Teaching tools like "
"Spinning Up help us make progress on both of these objectives."
msgstr ""
"OpenAI 的 mission_ 是確保通用人工智慧 (Artificial General Intelligence, AGI) "
"的安全發展，以及更廣泛地讓 AI 的益處普惠大眾。像 Spinning Up 這樣的教學"
"工具幫助我們在這兩個目標上取得進展。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:55
msgid ""
"To begin with, we move closer to broad distribution of benefits any time "
"we help people understand what AI is and how it works. This empowers "
"people to think critically about the many issues we anticipate will arise"
" as AI becomes more sophisticated and important in our lives."
msgstr ""
"首先，每當我們幫助人們理解 AI 是什麼以及它如何運作時，我們就更接近於"
"讓益處普惠大眾的目標。這使人們有能力批判性地思考我們預期隨著 AI 變得"
"更加精密和重要而將出現的許多議題。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:57
msgid ""
"Also, critically, `we need people to help "
"<https://jobs.lever.co/openai>`_ us work on making sure that AGI is safe."
" This requires a skill set which is currently in short supply because of "
"how new the field is. We know that many people are interested in helping "
"us, but don't know how---here is what you should study! If you can become"
" an expert on this material, you can make a difference on AI safety."
msgstr ""
"同樣關鍵的是，\\ `we need people to help "
"<https://jobs.lever.co/openai>`_\\ 我們致力於確保 AGI 的安全。由於這個領域"
"太新，目前所需的技能組合供不應求。我們知道很多人有興趣幫助我們，但不知道"
"該怎麼做——這就是你應該學習的內容！如果你能成為這些教材的專家，你就能"
"在 AI 安全方面發揮影響力。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:62
msgid "Code Design Philosophy"
msgstr "程式碼設計理念"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:64
msgid "The algorithm implementations in the Spinning Up repo are designed to be"
msgstr "Spinning Up 程式庫中的演算法實作被設計為"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:66
msgid "as simple as possible while still being reasonably good,"
msgstr "在保持相當好的效能的同時盡可能簡單，"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:67
msgid ""
"and highly-consistent with each other to expose fundamental similarities "
"between algorithms."
msgstr "並且彼此之間高度一致，以揭示演算法之間的根本相似性。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:69
msgid ""
"They are almost completely self-contained, with virtually no common code "
"shared between them (except for logging, saving, loading, and `MPI "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Message_Passing_Interface>`_ utilities), "
"so that an interested person can study each algorithm separately without "
"having to dig through an endless chain of dependencies to see how "
"something is done. The implementations are patterned so that they come as"
" close to pseudocode as possible, to minimize the gap between theory and "
"code."
msgstr ""
"它們幾乎完全是自包含的，彼此之間幾乎沒有共用程式碼（除了日誌記錄、"
"儲存、載入和 `MPI "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Message_Passing_Interface>`_ 工具之外），"
"這樣有興趣的人可以單獨研究每個演算法，而不必挖掘無盡的依賴鏈來了解某件"
"事是如何完成的。這些實作的編排方式盡可能接近虛擬碼 (Pseudocode)，"
"以最小化理論與程式碼之間的差距。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:71
msgid ""
"Importantly, they're all structured similarly, so if you clearly "
"understand one, jumping into the next is painless."
msgstr ""
"重要的是，它們的結構都很相似，所以如果你完全理解了其中一個，"
"跳到下一個就毫無障礙。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:73
msgid ""
"We tried to minimize the number of tricks used in each algorithm's "
"implementation, and minimize the differences between otherwise-similar "
"algorithms. To give some examples of removed tricks: we omit "
"regularization_ terms present in the original Soft-Actor Critic code, as "
"well as `observation normalization`_ from all algorithms. For an example "
"of where we've removed differences between algorithms: our "
"implementations of DDPG, TD3, and SAC all follow a convention of running "
"gradient descent updates after fixed intervals of environment "
"interaction. (By contrast, other public implementations of these "
"algorithms usually take slightly different approaches from each other, "
"making them a little bit harder to compare.)"
msgstr ""
"我們盡量減少每個演算法實作中使用的技巧，並盡量減少原本相似的演算法之間"
"的差異。舉一些移除技巧的例子：我們省略了原始 Soft-Actor Critic 程式碼中的 "
"regularization_ 項，以及所有演算法中的\\ `observation normalization`_\\ 。"
"關於我們消除演算法間差異的例子：我們的 DDPG、TD3 和 SAC 實作都遵循在"
"固定間隔的環境互動之後執行梯度下降 (Gradient Descent) 更新的慣例。"
"（相比之下，這些演算法的其他公開實作通常彼此之間採用略有不同的方法，"
"使它們稍微難以比較。）"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:75
msgid ""
"All algorithms are \"reasonably good\" in the sense that they achieve "
"roughly the intended performance, but don't necessarily match the best "
"reported results in the literature on every task. Consequently, be "
"careful if using any of these implementations for scientific benchmarking"
" comparisons. Details on each implementation's specific performance level"
" can be found on our `benchmarks`_ page."
msgstr ""
"所有演算法都是「相當好的」，意思是它們大致達到了預期的效能，但不一定"
"在每個任務上都能匹配文獻中報告的最佳結果。因此，如果將這些實作用於科學"
"基準測試 (Benchmark) 比較，請務必謹慎。每個實作的具體效能水準的詳細資訊"
"可以在我們的\\ `benchmarks`_\\ 頁面找到。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:79
msgid "Long-Term Support and Support History"
msgstr "長期支援與支援歷史"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:81
msgid ""
"Spinning Up is currently in maintenance mode. If there are any breaking "
"bugs, we'll repair them to ensure that Spinning Up can continue to help "
"people study deep RL."
msgstr ""
"Spinning Up 目前處於維護模式。如果出現任何嚴重的錯誤，我們會進行修復，"
"以確保 Spinning Up 能繼續幫助人們學習 deep RL。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:83
msgid "Support history so far:"
msgstr "目前為止的支援歷史："

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:85
msgid "**Nov 8, 2018:** Initial release!"
msgstr "**Nov 8, 2018：** 初始發布！"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:87
msgid ""
"**Nov, 2018:** Release was followed by a three-week period of high-"
"bandwidth support."
msgstr ""
"**Nov, 2018：** 發布後接續了為期三週的高強度支援期。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:89
msgid ""
"**April, 2019:** Approximately six months after release, we conducted an "
"internal review of Spinning Up based on feedback from the community. The "
"review surfaced interest in a few key features:"
msgstr ""
"**April, 2019：** 發布約六個月後，我們根據社群的回饋對 Spinning Up "
"進行了內部審查。審查中浮現了對幾個關鍵功能的興趣："

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:91
msgid ""
"**Implementations in Other Neural Network Libraries.** Several people "
"expressed interest in seeing Spinning Up use alternatives to Tensorflow "
"v1 for the RL implementations. A few members of the community even "
"developed their own PyTorch versions of Spinning Up algorithms, such as "
"Kashif Rasul's `Fired Up`_,  Kai Arulkumaran's `Spinning Up Basic`_, and "
"Misha Laskin's `Torching Up`_. As a result, making this kind of \"Rosetta"
" Stone\" for deep RL became a high priority for future work."
msgstr ""
"**使用其他神經網路函式庫的實作。** 一些人表達了希望 Spinning Up 使用 "
"Tensorflow v1 以外的替代方案來實作 RL 的興趣。社群中甚至有幾位成員開發了"
"自己的 PyTorch 版本 Spinning Up 演算法，例如 Kashif Rasul 的 `Fired Up`_、"
"Kai Arulkumaran 的 `Spinning Up Basic`_，以及 Misha Laskin 的 "
"`Torching Up`_。因此，為 deep RL 製作這種「羅塞塔石碑」"
"成為了未來工作的高優先事項。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:93
msgid ""
"**Open Source RL Environments.** Many people expressed an interest in "
"seeing Spinning Up use more open source RL environments (eg `PyBullet`_) "
"for benchmarks, examples, and exercises."
msgstr ""
"**開源 RL 環境 (Environment)。** 許多人表達了希望 Spinning Up 使用更多"
"開源 RL 環境（例如 `PyBullet`_）來進行基準測試、範例和練習的興趣。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:95
msgid ""
"**More Algorithms.** There was some interest in seeing other algorithms "
"included in Spinning Up, especially Deep Q-Networks."
msgstr ""
"**更多演算法。** 一些人對在 Spinning Up 中加入其他演算法感興趣，"
"特別是 Deep Q-Networks。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:97
msgid "**Jan, 2020:** The PyTorch update to Spinning Up was released!"
msgstr "**Jan, 2020：** Spinning Up 的 PyTorch 更新版本發布了！"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:99
msgid ""
"**Future:** No major updates are currently planned for Spinning Up. In "
"the event it makes sense for us to release an additional update, "
"following what we found in the 6-month review, the next-highest priority "
"features are to focus more on open source RL environments and adding "
"algorithms."
msgstr ""
"**未來：** 目前沒有計劃對 Spinning Up 進行重大更新。如果我們決定發布額外"
"的更新，根據我們在六個月審查中的發現，下一個最高優先級的功能是更多地"
"關注開源 RL 環境和新增演算法。"

#: ../../user/introduction.rst:101
msgid ""
"Additionally, as discussed in the blog post, Spinning Up has been "
"integrated into the curriculum for our Scholars_ and Fellows_ programs."
msgstr ""
"此外，如部落格文章中所述，Spinning Up 已被納入我們的 Scholars_ 和 "
"Fellows_ 計畫的課程中。"
